<h1 id="english">What's up <%= @user.username? %></h1>

<p>Congrats! Your request to manage <%= @venue.name %> has been approved by our moderators. You can now edit your venue’s information at anytime by clicking ‘edit this venue’ at the very bottom of your venue’s profile page (please note, you must be logged in to see this option). To see a list of all the events / venues / profiles you manage, simply log in and go to ‘Your Page’ (under ‘account’ in the main menu, again you must be logged in to see this). Make sure to keep your venue profile up to date so your customers (both new and old) know where to find you and what you are up to.</p>

<p>As a user of DoIndie you can also add all your upcoming shows to our show calendar by simply logging in and submitting your gig details here : <a href="http://doindie.co.kr/en/venues/new">http://doindie.co.kr/en/venues/new</a>. It takes just a few short minutes to create an event on DoIndie. We have thousands of visitors to our site every month. So what are you waiting for, submit your show and get promoting now ;)</p>

<p>We now have a ‘fan profile’ feature on DoIndie, where DoIndie users will be able to follow you venue. People who ‘like’ your venue page on DoIndie will be able to keep up to date with all your gigs in their own personalized gig calendar. For now, our ‘fan profiles’ simply offer users a personalized gig calendar (showing only shows from bands & venues they have ‘liked’), however, we will soon be implementing a ‘news feed’ feature where we will inform users about all your comings and goings, news, gigs, etc. In the future, as our ‘fan profile’ feature develops we are confident it will become a great tool for connecting your venue with the people who matter most, your customers. Please encourage people to sign up and ‘like’ your venue by sharing your new profile with them on facebook, twitter etc.</p>

<p>As well as the ‘fan profiles’ mentioned above, we have loads of other cool new features in the works, including the following : </p>
<p>
- Auto export your DoIndie shows to a facebook ‘tab’ in your venue’s facebook page.<br>
- A Shop to sell advanced tickets to people (in both Korean and English)<br>
- Ability to upload pictures to your profile<br>
- DoIndie mixtapes to help fans discover new bands<br>

- and many, many more.
</p>


<p>If you have any special shows coming up (like an anniversary show etc), please do not hesitate to contact us as we are always happy to help promote local venues. Additionally if you have any important news to tell everyone, please let us know. We would love to feature you in our news section <a href="http://doindie.co.kr/en/blog">http://doindie.co.kr/en/blog</a>.</p>

<p>Thanks again for using Doindie. Please tell your friends about us and help us to build this website into a long lasting pillar of the local Korean Music scene. DoIndie is always striving to develop and improve, if you have any advice, spot any mistakes on the website or want to suggest some new features to us, please drop us a message any time.</p>

<p>Thanks for using DoIndie. Have a great day! </p>

